description:
&lt;p&gt;Moorfields Eye Hospital NHSFT has expanded their Private Patient Division with the addition of 2 brand-new theatres at Moorfields Eye Hospital, City Road site. We are looking for a highly experienced, motivated, forward thinking, ODP/Registered Nurses to work in these purpose-built, dedicated Private Patient Operating Theatres.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For this Band 6 post, successful candidates will be employed on AFC national terms and conditions, encompassing all of the standard NHS Benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are committed to ongoing professional development and opportunities exist to undertake a wide range of in-house and external courses. Rotational opportunities throughout the other ophthalmic departments that make up Moorfields Private Theatres can be accommodated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidates will need to have both Anaesthetic and Recovery experience, extensive paediatric experience, excellent communications skills, be highly motivated, demonstrates good leadership and committed to the delivery of high quality care within all areas of the ophthalmic theatre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidates will hold the appropriate qualifications to be a current registered practitioner (RGN/ODP) and demonstrate evidence of continuing professional development and mentoring qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMay MallariJob titleTheatre ManagerEmail addressmay.mallari1@nhs.netTelephone number07711 765374Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion or visit, please contact May Mallari-Theatre Manager for Moorfields Private on 07711 765374 or email: may.mallari1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
